64.0	Tony_Kushner	Tony Kushner	Anthony Robert "Tony" Kushner (born July 16, 1956) is an American playwright and screenwriter. He received the Pulitzer Prize for Drama in 1993 for his play Angels in America: A Gay Fantasia on National Themes and co-authored with Eric Roth the screenplay for the 2005 film Munich.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4a/Tony_Kushner_and_Angels_in_America%27s_20th_Anniversary.jpg/220px-Tony_Kushner_and_Angels_in_America%27s_20th_Anniversary.jpg
